<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[795,1388,2892,3316]" pageId="24" pageNumber="82">
Until very recently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" box="[1069,1213,3006,3039]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Casinycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="argynnis">C. argynnis</taxonomicName>
was the only species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" box="[943,1091,3046,3079]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Casinycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Casinycteris</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
